cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face spoofing detection using novel features. The use of binocular depth and micro-texture features also suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms for template face registration and spatial pyramid coding, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques for multi-modal face spoofing detection could also suggest that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of image processing techniques for feature extraction could place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
